<br>
I really hate to say this kind of comment, been holding off on putting it in any of this kind of threads, but if you don't like the class, start a new one. Or, learn to adapt to this one and stop complaining about it.<br>
<br>
Look at the big picture. This game needs defined roles for classes in raid situations.<br>
<br>
Yeah, some of the abilities have changed since release. But those who say they 'created their mage for x reason, not y reason' seem like senseless whining to me. I mean, did you really know about anything in the end game when you made your mage? Did you *really* know how things worked, having experience in them? <br>
<br>
No, you didn't really know how things worked. Unless you already had a high level character, in which case, you wouldn't be whining, you'd be going back to play that character.<br>
<br>
When *I* made *MY* mage, I didn't know anything about anything.<br>
<br>
For most of my life, mages did nothing but damage.<br>
<br>
Now we actually have some role, some place in the game, and, and this is the important part, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> we not only still do damage, we do better damage than we ever did before</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Dunno who can complain about the mage class... if you want to do damage, you have TWO options<br>
1)Make a new twink of a class which does nothing but dmg<br>
2)Nuke with your mage<br>
